column1: # The results of 100 simulations using each of EvolvAGene and INDELible alignments, aligned with Clustal, MUSCLE and Mafft with local and global settings and trimmed with GBlocks, TrimAl and ZORRO plus CIAlign with relaxed, moderate and stringent settings.
# Number of positions: total number of positions in the alignment
# Alignment_Tool: Software used to align the sequences
# Trimming Tool: Tool used to trim the alignments, Relaxed, Moderate and Stringent are CIAlign with parameter settings as listed in Supplementary Table 2, None means without running any trimmer.
# Correct_Pairs_Removed: the proportion of correctly aligned pairs of residues in the test alignment which are removed by CIAlign
# Nt_Removed, Gaps_Removed, Positions_Removed: proportion of non-gap positions, gap positions, all positions removed by the trimming tool, respectively
